itle> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_money.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: FV economy really screwed up</span><hr size=1> Things to remember about the FV ruleset:<br>
<br>
1) No Alts - Players can only have 1 character per acct.  This drastically increases the amount of armor and weapons that are available, because a lot of it is stuff that would normally end up on a player's alt rather than for sale.  This deflates the price of dropped gear.<br>
<br>
2) Removal of No-drop - Again, this drastically increases the amount of armor and weapons available.  Further deflating the price of dropped gear.<br>
<br>
3) TLC - A lot of tradeskill components are flagged MAGIC and subject to TLC.  This inflates their price because level 60's can't just go farm them.<br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwikkin23.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wikkin23</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 265<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/9/02 10:12:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1511.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: FV economy really screwed up</span><hr size=1> My guild also keeps a vendor in the bazaar who's prices are (what we consider) extremely high. We do this so that our guild can see what we have in our &quot;guildbank.&quot; If a guildie sees something in there that he/she wants, they let an officer know, and they get that item.<br>
